    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-23T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="174"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/2708: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-23T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 23, 1942—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:51 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>692. I failed to state in my 687 yesterday: It was also agreed between President
                    Santos and me that in event of necessity of General Andrews ordering United
                    States Army or Navy craft to enter Colombian territorial waters General López
                    would be immediately notified in detail regarding destination, description et
                    cetera of the forces involved so that he in turn could at once advise the
                    President.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Panama for General Andrews.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
